```suggestion
and `D` is a (not necessarily commutative) `K`-algebra.
```

```suggestion
In fact ideals of `K` immediately give rise to nontrivial quotients of `D` so there are no central simple
algebras in this case according to our definition, if K is not a field. The theory of central simple algebras
really is a theory over fields.
```
This lemma is a bit weird because necessarily k and K are both the centre of D. Is it really useful?
I have changed the lemma to say if `D/K/k` is a tower, then `D` central simple over `k` implies `K=k`
It still feels a weird theorem though

How about introduce an Algebra.IsCentral class and combine it with IsSimpleRing? I think it makes little sense of bundling these two only, as you usually want to assume FiniteDimensional as well (to define the Brauer group etc.) 
Some results maybe holds more generally for artinian simple algebras, as those as semisimple.
I ended up just removing `Algebra.IsCentralSimple` as that instance does not imply `IsSimpleRing D` for not able to find synthesation orders
I have added some docs
Results in this file still hold for IsCentral algebras, I think.
the last one needs non-tiriviality, other than that everything generalizes

```suggestion
- `Algebra.IsCentral.self`: a commutative ring is a central algebra over itself.
```

These hold in the original setting [CommSemiring K] [Semiring D] right? Just place them below the definition.
```suggestion
@[simp]
lemma center_eq_bot : Subalgebra.center K D = âŠ¥ := eq_bot_iff.2 IsCentral.out

variable {D} in
lemma mem_center_iff {x : D} : x âˆˆ Subalgebra.center K D â†” âˆƒ (a : K), x = algebraMap K D a := by
  rw [center_eq_bot, Algebra.mem_bot]
  simp [eq_comm]

instance self : IsCentral K K where
  out x := by simp [Algebra.mem_bot]
```

```suggestion
we prove something is central simple, there we don't need to prove `âŠ¥ â‰¤ center K D` even though this
```
sounds nicer to me
Should we not add [FiniteDimensional K D] here?
Some results does not require finite dimensional assumption. I have added a bit more docs. Thanks

```suggestion
For a commutative ring `K` and a `K`-algebra `D`, we say that `D` is a central algebra over `K` if
the center of `D` is the image of `K` in `D`.
```
